(549, 'Java Team Leader', 'Ho Chi Minh', '  Salary:   Attractive    ', 'We are looking for a skilled Java Team Leader to join our ranks. The services we provide are all client-facing, so a high attention to usability and customer satisfaction is expected. If you want to work closely with a team, drive ideas to completion, and be a core member who creates our next-generation software services, then contact us. We are looking to build upon our 15 years of experience and deliver new features and functionality to our services. To do this, we want a Senior Java Architect who is dedicated, self-motivated, analytical, and takes pride in the fruits of his or her labor. We are looking for a person with design experience. Our tech stack relies on Oracle, Java, Tomcat, and Flex at the core; so experience with these technologies is a major plus.  RESPONSIBILITIES INCLUDE: \r\nâ€¢ Communicating with the customer (in English) to get requirements, to discuss technical aspects, issues and to give technical solutions \r\nâ€¢ Comprehensively reading of requirement specifications/use cases, writing technical specifications, designing in compliance with established quality standard of the company. \r\nâ€¢ To lead the technical design of the solution, ensuring that it is well structured, consistent and appropriate for purpose and platform. \r\nâ€¢ To ensure that software and platform design is considered before changes are made, to update the design as required and to ensure that coding reflects the design. \r\nâ€¢ Giving technical support to team members \r\nâ€¢ Follow all phases of the software development cycle: requirements analysis, functional design, technical design, implementation, documentation, software QA, maintenance and support. \r\nâ€¢ Report to a project lead or manager. \r\nâ€¢ Must have strong written and verbal communication skills. \r\nâ€¢ Data warehouse design and implementation. \r\nâ€¢ Works closely with a small team in a collaborative environment. ', ' Manager , Java , J2EE ', 0, ' Your Skills and Experience â€¢ Bachelorâ€™s degree in Computer Science or a related field. \r\nâ€¢ Candidate must have a minimum of 4+ years of software engineering experience using Java. \r\nâ€¢ Exposure to standard patterns and practices \r\nâ€¢ Experience with design, development, unit testing \r\nâ€¢ Strong Oracle SQL/PLSQL and JDBC experience \r\nâ€¢ OOD proficiency \r\nâ€¢ Hibernate experience (ORM) \r\nâ€¢ DB Relational proficiency (DML/DDL) \r\nâ€¢ J2EE (Servlets, Web Services, Containers, Tomcat/Apache) \r\nâ€¢ Software refactoring with design patterns experience  IDEAL REQUIREMENTS: \r\nâ€¢ Familiarity with claims processing and health care technology \r\nâ€¢ Adobe Flex and Action-script experience  ', ' Why You''ll Love Working Here Join us to get:  \r\nCompetitive salary compensation  \r\nDevelopment in technical skill  \r\nWork with talented guys  \r\nBe one of the key members to creat our further developement ', '2015-07-22 16:23:19', 'https://itviec.com/jobs/manager-j2ee-java-team-leader'),
(550, 'Senior iOS Developer', 'Others', '  Salary:   Between 1,000-2,000 USD    ', 'Relocation to Bangkok, Visa + Work permit provided.  We''re looking for a Senior iOS Developer to join our amazing team!  If you like to work in a team, consider yourself a team player, and are curious about new cool technology, this is the right place for you.  Full range of technologies to work on and learn. Our projects use different technologies and operate in different industries.  ** Working location: Bangkok, Thailand', ' iOS , Software Architect , Team Leader ', 0, ' Your Skills and Experience - Interested to learn new technologies, ethical hacking, scalability and agile methodologies.  \r\n- Has knowledge of Objective C. If you know swift, it would be great. \r\n- State of the art libraries \r\n- Love clean code \r\n- 3+ years of experience  \r\n- At least two apps already published in AppStore \r\n- Able to communicate in english ', ' Why You''ll Love Working Here If you like to work in a team, consider yourself a team player, and are curious about new cool technology, this is the right place for you.  We have some awesome perks too!  - We provide a brand new macbook pro, brand new mobile device for mobile dev.  \r\n- Free lunch on Fridays, drinks and snacks every day.  \r\n- Hacking time to explore new technologies you are interested to learn \r\n- If you travel to any of the cities in Japan, Indonesia or Thailand where our hotel partner operates we extend our company''s rate to you and your family.  \r\n- Come and play Call of Duty in PS 4 with or let''s see if you can beat anyone in the team playing in FIFA 15 :) ', '2015-07-22 16:23:20', 'https://itviec.com/jobs/software-architect-team-leader-senior-ios-developer'),
