(569, 'Lead PHP Developer', 'Ho Chi Minh', '  Salary:   Depends on Experience    ', 'This is an exciting new role with a generous package leading a small development team for an Australian company. You will have superior coding skills but more importantly will be able to design solutions and be confident in communicating these solutions to internal team members as well as clients.  You will be expected to: \r\n- Understand customer needs and help define the right technical solution keeping in mind security and performance constraints  \r\n- Have strong PHP skills and probably some frameworks (preferably Laravel) \r\n- Have awesome database skills (primarily MySQL but also some exposure to NoSQL will be advantageous) \r\n- Create and maintain technical documentation for projects as they progress  \r\n- Contribute to architecture, database design, application design and web app development  \r\n- Personally take responsibility for developing critical features in a project  \r\n- Be hands on with coding, implementation, unit testing, maintenance, and troubleshooting  \r\n- Assist our Project Managers in deploying the application on staging and live servers  \r\n- Meet tight deadlines \r\n- Understand the basics of systems administration (LAMP environment, Cloud deployment) \r\n- Be able to contribute to diagnosing system faults \r\n- Confident in your abilities as a developer, humble in your approach to teamwork and collaboration  This is a senior role in a growing organisation with international clients. You will be expected to contribute at that level. ', ' PHP , Team Leader , MySQL ', 0, ' Your Skills and Experience  - High level of hands on understanding in PHP, Laravel, MySQL and Web Services \r\n - 7+ years experience as a developer \r\n - Proven understanding of the standards required to deliver for international companies \r\n - Solid experiencing delivering development projects  \r\n - Understands infrastructure and deployment - especially LAMP stack \r\n - Ex