(732, 'Program Manager (.Net, Business Analyst)', 'Ho Chi Minh', '  Salary:   Very Attractive    ', 'We are looking for a Program Manager that can support a high performance environment and create positive synergy with their colleagues. This person is driven, has a can-do attitude and high standards for excellence coupled with the ability to harness teamwork for higher achievements. At Niteco, the Program Manager oversees the full project management life cycle and software development life cycle for the implementation of multiple highly complex, large-scale, strategic IT and business initiatives. The Program Manager manages four to eight project teams, reports to the Senior Management Team (SLT), and takes a leadership role in the following:  â€¢	Implementation of established policies, system monitors and controls to ensure successful management and reporting of all corporate initiatives in the program. \r\nâ€¢	Supervision and leadership of program and project staff to oversee the impacts and interdependencies to ensure initiatives meet goals and objectives of SLT while ensuring customer satisfaction at the highest level. \r\nâ€¢	Contribution to continuous process improvements for projects within the program and programs across the project delivery organization.   RESPONSIBILITIES  â€¢	Interactive with internal customers and consultative value to our business partners. \r\nâ€¢	Provide project management mentorship for team leads and project managers within the program and strategic alignment of projects to business needs. \r\nâ€¢	Establish and implement metrics that measure project performance. \r\nâ€¢	Conduct project status review meetings and tracking of the open points and assigned taskâ€™s status. \r\nâ€¢	Work with Project Managers to review, determine the project health by measuring the variance in scope, schedule, cost and quality from the respective baselines. \r\nâ€¢	Conduct periodic project and process audits in conjunction with the company QA team. \r\nâ€¢